## CSS Principles

### Scope

-   Covers atomic/utility CSS, Tailwind compatibility, and Perchance-specific best practices.
-   Outlines maintainable, scalable styling for Perchance apps.
-   References atomic CSS utilities and Tailwind docs.

---

## Core Principles

-   **Shoelace & Pico.css:**
    Use Shoelace for advanced UI components and Pico.css for base styling. Atomic/utility CSS is still encouraged for custom utilities and rapid prototyping.
-   **Atomic/Utility CSS:**  
    Use single-purpose classes for styling (e.g., `.p-2`, `.text-center`).
-   **No @import:**  
    Merge all CSS into a single file for deployment.
-   **Tailwind Compatibility:**  
    Use Tailwind or similar utility frameworks for rapid prototyping.
-   **Minimal Bloat:**  
    Only include styles actually used in the app.

---

## Best Practices

-   Organize CSS by utility and component.
-   Use variables for colors, spacing, and fonts.
-   Test styles in the Perchance editor before deployment.
-   Avoid `!important` unless absolutely necessary.

---

## Example

```css
/* Atomic utility class */
.p-2 { padding: 0.5rem; }
.text-center { text-align: center; }
.bg-primary { background: #4f46e5; }
```

